cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL

This paper deals with the curation of Twitter user lists, which involves analyzing the Twitter network and identifying authoritative commentators on a particular topic. This falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), social and community computing (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could also place it under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on social media and network analysis, the first four sub-categories are more likely.
